SELECT AIRLINEalias0.AIRLINE_CODE, COUNT(*) AS FLIGHT_COUNT
FROM AIRLINE AS AIRLINEalias0
JOIN FLIGHT AS FLIGHTalias0 ON AIRLINEalias0.AIRLINE_CODE = FLIGHTalias0.AIRLINE_CODE
JOIN FARE AS FAREalias0 ON FLIGHTalias0.FLIGHT_ID = FAREalias0.FLIGHT_ID
JOIN FARE_BASIS AS FARE_BASISalias0 ON FAREalias0.FARE_BASIS_CODE = FARE_BASISalias0.FARE_BASIS_CODE
WHERE FARE_BASISalias0.SEASON = 'seasonal' AND FARE_BASISalias0.DISCOUNTED = 'discounted'
GROUP BY AIRLINEalias0.AIRLINE_CODE
ORDER BY FLIGHT_COUNT DESC
LIMIT 1

SELECT AIRLINEalias0.AIRLINE_CODE FROM AIRLINE AS AIRLINEalias0 WHERE AIRLINEalias0.AIRLINE_CODE IN (SELECT FAREalias0.FARE_AIRLINE FROM FARE AS FAREalias0 WHERE FAREalias0.SEASON = "seasonal" AND FAREalias0.DISCOUNTED = "yes" GROUP BY FAREalias0.FARE_AIRLINE HAVING COUNT(*) = (SELECT MAX(flight_count) FROM (SELECT COUNT(*) AS flight_count FROM FARE WHERE SEASON = "seasonal" AND DISCOUNTED = "yes" GROUP BY FARE_AIRLINE) AS temp_table))

SELECT AIRLINE.AIRLINE_CODE
FROM AIRLINE
WHERE AIRLINE.AIRLINE_CODE IN (
    SELECT FLIGHT.airline_code
    FROM FLIGHT
    WHERE FLIGHT.airline_code IN (
        SELECT FARE.fare_airline
        FROM FARE
        WHERE FARE.restriction_code = "season"
    )
    GROUP BY FLIGHT.airline_code
    ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
    LIMIT 1
)

SELECT AIRLINE.AIRLINE_CODE, COUNT(DISTINCT FLIGHT.FLIGHT_ID) AS TOTAL_SEASONAL_DISCOUNT_FLIGHTS
FROM AIRLINE
JOIN FLIGHT ON AIRLINE.AIRLINE_CODE = FLIGHT.AIRLINE_CODE
JOIN FARE ON FLIGHT.FLIGHT_ID = FARE.FLIGHT_ID
JOIN FARE_BASIS ON FARE.FARE_BASIS_CODE = FARE_BASIS.FARE_BASIS_CODE
WHERE FARE_BASIS.SEASON = 'Y'
GROUP BY AIRLINE.AIRLINE_CODE
ORDER BY TOTAL_SEASONAL_DISCOUNT_FLIGHTS DESC
LIMIT 1

SELECT DISTINCT AIRLINEalias0.AIRLINE_CODE 
FROM AIRLINE AS AIRLINEalias0 
WHERE AIRLINEalias0.AIRLINE_CODE IN 
(
    SELECT FLIGHTalias0.AIRLINE_CODE 
    FROM FLIGHT AS FLIGHTalias0 
    WHERE FLIGHTalias0.FLIGHT_ID IN 
    (
        SELECT FLIGHT_FAREalias0.FLIGHT_ID 
        FROM FLIGHT_FARE AS FLIGHT_FAREalias0 
        WHERE FLIGHT_FAREalias0.FARE_ID IN 
        (
            SELECT FAREalias0.FARE_ID 
            FROM FARE AS FAREalias0 
            WHERE FAREalias0.ONE_DIRECTION_COST IN 
            (
                SELECT MIN(FAREalias1.ONE_DIRECTION_COST) 
                FROM FARE AS FAREalias1 
                WHERE FAREalias1.SEASON = 'seasonal_discount'
            )
        )
    )
)

WHERE AIRLINEalias0.AIRLINE_CODE = (
    SELECT FLIGHTalias0.AIRLINE_CODE
    FROM FLIGHT AS FLIGHTalias0
    GROUP BY FLIGHTalias0.AIRLINE_CODE
    ORDER BY COUNT(FLIGHTalias0.FLIGHT_ID) DESC
    LIMIT 1
)

SELECT AIRLINEalias0.AIRLINE_NAME 
FROM AIRLINE AS AIRLINEalias0 
WHERE AIRLINEalias0.AIRLINE_CODE = (
    SELECT FLIGHTalias0.AIRLINE_CODE 
    FROM FLIGHT AS FLIGHTalias0 
    GROUP BY FLIGHTalias0.AIRLINE_CODE 
    ORDER BY COUNT(FLIGHTalias0.FLIGHT_ID) DESC 
    LIMIT 1
)

SELECT AIRLINE.airline_name
FROM AIRLINE
WHERE AIRLINE.airline_code = (
    SELECT flight.airline_code
    FROM (
        SELECT airline_code, COUNT(*) AS num_flights
        FROM flight
        GROUP BY airline_code
        ORDER BY num_flights DESC
        LIMIT 1
    ) AS max_flights
)

SELECT AIRLINE.airline_name, COUNT(FLIGHT.flight_id) AS num_flights
FROM AIRLINE
JOIN FLIGHT ON AIRLINE.airline_code = FLIGHT.airline_code
GROUP BY AIRLINE.airline_name
ORDER BY num_flights DESC
LIMIT 1

SELECT AVG(f.DEPARTURE_TIME) AS average_departure_time, d.DAY_NAME
FROM flight f
JOIN airport_service a ON f.from_airport = a.airport_code
JOIN city c ON a.city_code = c.city_code
JOIN days d ON f.flight_days = d.days_code
WHERE c.city_name = "bna"
AND f.DEPARTURE_TIME BETWEEN '01/01/1990' AND '12/31/1990'
GROUP BY d.DAY_NAME

SELECT AVG(f.DEPARTURE_TIME) AS weekly_avg_departure_time, d.DAY_NAME
FROM flight f
JOIN airport_service a ON f.from_airport = a.airport_code
JOIN city c ON a.city_code = c.city_code
JOIN days d ON f.flight_days = d.days_code
WHERE c.city_name = "bna" AND f.DEPARTURE_TIME >= DATE_SUB(CURDATE(), INTERVAL 1 YEAR)
GROUP BY d.DAY_NAME

SELECT AVG(f.DEPARTURE_TIME) as weekly_avg_departure_time, MONTH(d.year) as month_number
FROM flight f
JOIN airport_service a ON f.FROM_AIRPORT = a.AIRPORT_CODE
JOIN city c ON a.CITY_CODE = c.CITY_CODE
JOIN date_day d ON f.DEPARTURE_TIME = d.day_name
WHERE c.CITY_NAME = "bna"
GROUP BY MONTH(d.year)
ORDER BY d.year DESC

SELECT AIRCRAFTalias0.AIRCRAFT_CODE, COUNT(FLIGHTalias0.FLIGHT_ID) AS FREQUENCY, MONTHalias0.MONTH_NAME
FROM AIRCRAFT AS AIRCRAFTalias0
INNER JOIN EQUIPMENT_SEQUENCE AS EQUIPMENT_SEQUENCEalias0 ON EQUIPMENT_SEQUENCEalias0.AIRCRAFT_CODE = AIRCRAFTalias0.AIRCRAFT_CODE
INNER JOIN FLIGHT AS FLIGHTalias0 ON FLIGHTalias0.AIRCRAFT_CODE_SEQUENCE = EQUIPMENT_SEQUENCEalias0.AIRCRAFT_CODE_SEQUENCE
INNER JOIN DATE_DAY AS DATE_DAYalias0 ON FLIGHTalias0.FLIGHT_DAYS = DATE_DAYalias0.DAY_NAME
INNER JOIN MONTH AS MONTHalias0 ON DATE_DAYalias0.MONTH_NUMBER = MONTHalias0.MONTH_NUMBER
GROUP BY AIRCRAFTalias0.AIRCRAFT_CODE, MONTHalias0.MONTH_NAME

JOIN EQUIPMENT_SEQUENCE ON AIRCRAFT.aircraft_code = EQUIPMENT_SEQUENCE.aircraft_code
JOIN FLIGHT ON EQUIPMENT_SEQUENCE.aircraft_code_sequence = FLIGHT.aircraft_code_sequence
JOIN DATE_DAY ON FLIGHT.flight_days = DATE_DAY.days_code
JOIN MONTH ON DATE_DAY.month_number = MONTH.month_number
GROUP BY AIRCRAFT.aircraft_code, MONTH.month_name

JOIN FLIGHT AS FLIGHTalias0 ON FLIGHTalias0.AIRCRAFT_CODE_SEQUENCE = EQUIPMENT_SEQUENCEalias0.AIRCRAFT_CODE_SEQUENCE
JOIN DATE_DAY AS DATE_DAYalias0 ON FLIGHTalias0.FLIGHT_DAYS = DATE_DAYalias0.DAYS_CODE

JOIN FLIGHT ON EQUIPMENT_SEQUENCE.AIRCRAFT_CODE_SEQUENCE = FLIGHT.AIRCRAFT_CODE_SEQUENCE 
JOIN AIRPORT_SERVICE ON FLIGHT.FROM_AIRPORT = AIRPORT_SERVICE.AIRPORT_CODE 
JOIN STATE ON AIRPORT_SERVICE.STATE_CODE = STATE.STATE_CODE 
WHERE STATE.COUNTRY_NAME = "usa" 
GROUP BY AIRCRAFT.AIRCRAFT_CODE 
ORDER BY frequency DESC 
LIMIT 1

SELECT aircraft.manufacturer, COUNT(*) AS count 
FROM aircraft 
INNER JOIN equipment_sequence 
ON aircraft.aircraft_code = equipment_sequence.aircraft_code 
INNER JOIN flight 
ON equipment_sequence.aircraft_code_sequence = flight.aircraft_code_sequence 
INNER JOIN airport_service 
ON flight.from_airport = airport_service.airport_code 
INNER JOIN state 
ON airport_service.state_code = state.state_code 
WHERE state.country_name = "USA" 
GROUP BY aircraft.manufacturer 
ORDER BY count DESC 
LIMIT 1

The usual steps for aircraft takeoff and landing involve the following:

1. Before takeoff:
- Aircraft is fueled and loaded with passengers and cargo.
- Pre-flight checks are conducted by the pilot and crew.
- Air traffic control clearance is obtained.
- Taxi to the runway and line up for takeoff.

2. During takeoff:
- Pilot increases throttle to accelerate the aircraft down the runway.
- Aircraft gains speed and lift, eventually becoming airborne.
- Gear is retracted and flaps are adjusted for climb.

3. In-flight:
- Aircraft climbs to cruising altitude and follows designated flight path.
- Communication with air traffic control for routing and updates.
- Monitoring of systems and instruments for safety and efficiency.

4. Before landing:
- Descent and approach to destination airport.
- Communication with air traffic control for landing clearance.
- Gear extended, flaps adjusted, and speed reduced for landing.

5. During landing:
- Aircraft aligns with runway and descends for touchdown.
- Flare and touchdown on runway.
- Reverse thrust and braking to slow down and taxi to terminal.

6. After landing:
- Taxi to gate for passenger disembarkation.
- Post-flight checks and inspections.
- Aircraft is refueled and prepared for next flight.

The steps for aircraft takeoff and landing typically involve the following:

1. Preparation and pre-flight checks: The pilot and crew perform pre-flight checks to ensure the aircraft is in proper working condition and all systems are functioning correctly.

2. Taxiing to the runway: The aircraft taxis from the terminal to the designated runway for takeoff. During taxiing, the pilot communicates with air traffic control for clearance.

3. Takeoff: The aircraft accelerates down the runway until it reaches the necessary speed for takeoff. The pilot then pulls back on the control yoke or stick to lift the aircraft off the ground.

4. Climb: After takeoff, the aircraft climbs to its designated cruising altitude. The pilot follows specific climb procedures to ensure a smooth ascent.

5. Cruise: Once at cruising altitude, the aircraft maintains a steady speed and altitude for the duration of the flight.

6. Descent: As the aircraft nears its destination, the pilot begins the descent process by reducing altitude and speed.

7. Approach and landing: The aircraft aligns with the runway and descends for landing. The pilot follows specific approach and landing procedures to safely touch down on the runway.

8. Taxiing to the terminal: After landing, the aircraft taxis from the runway to the terminal for passengers to disembark.

These steps may vary slightly depending on the specific aircraft, airport, and flight conditions.

SELECT airline.airline_name, AVG(flight.departure_time) as avg_delay_time
FROM airline
JOIN flight ON airline.airline_code = flight.airline_code
GROUP BY airline.airline_name
ORDER BY avg_delay_time ASC
LIMIT 1

SELECT AIRLINE.airline_name
FROM AIRLINE
JOIN (
    SELECT airline_code, AVG(departure_delay) AS avg_delay
    FROM FLIGHT
    GROUP BY airline_code
) AS avg_delays ON AIRLINE.airline_code = avg_delays.airline_code
WHERE avg_delays.avg_delay = (
    SELECT MIN(avg_delay)
    FROM (
        SELECT airline_code, AVG(departure_delay) AS avg_delay
        FROM FLIGHT
        GROUP BY airline_code
    ) AS avg_delays
)

SELECT AIRLINE_ALIAS.AIRLINE_NAME
FROM (
    SELECT FLIGHT.AIRLINE_CODE, AVG(FLIGHT.DEPARTURE_DELAY) AS AVG_DELAY
    FROM FLIGHT
    GROUP BY FLIGHT.AIRLINE_CODE
) AS AVG_DELAY_ALIAS
JOIN AIRLINE AS AIRLINE_ALIAS ON AVG_DELAY_ALIAS.AIRLINE_CODE = AIRLINE_ALIAS.AIRLINE_CODE
WHERE AVG_DELAY_ALIAS.AVG_DELAY = (
    SELECT MIN(AVG_DELAY)
    FROM (
        SELECT FLIGHT.AIRLINE_CODE, AVG(FLIGHT.DEPARTURE_DELAY) AS AVG_DELAY
        FROM FLIGHT
        GROUP BY FLIGHT.AIRLINE_CODE
    ) AS AVG_DELAY
)

SELECT AIRLINE.airline_name FROM AIRLINE JOIN (SELECT airline_code, AVG(departure_delay) AS avg_delay FROM FLIGHT GROUP BY airline_code) AS avg_delay_table ON AIRLINE.airline_code = avg_delay_table.airline_code ORDER BY avg_delay_table.avg_delay LIMIT 1

SELECT AIRLINE.airline_name 
FROM AIRLINE 
INNER JOIN FLIGHT ON AIRLINE.airline_code = FLIGHT.airline_code 
GROUP BY AIRLINE.airline_name 
ORDER BY AVG(FLIGHT.departure_time) ASC 
LIMIT 1
